Also, we are making arrangements for your child's classroom belongings to be returned to you. More details to follow.

If you have any questions, please contact the Front Office at (480) 641-2640.

Thank you,

Wow, SDA Fam! You know how to deliver on the mini challenge! We have some incredibly bright, clever, artistic, wise students, I’m verklempt. While each student demonstrated that perfect union of form and function, the winner with the most reacts is
...... 🥁.....SARIAH M and Sonya Maynes! Sariah’s perfectly timed, succinct message of hope, “Be the rainbow in someone else’s cloud,” literally brought bright color across our paths. Congratulations

Also, big win to Naomi Medina Goodwin and her children! They scored a very large number of positive reacts so they win the employee category! Congrats !!

And a big runner up to Mich Hernandez and Petra for wholly embodying the spirit of the challenge by completing it before it started. To see what I mean, see the screenshot below of Petra at the Piano. Congrats

Awesome job, everyone!
REMINDER: I hope you are working on your famous building project! Submissions are due by Friday!

post_text:
￼MINI CHALLENGE - WRITE YOUR PASSION. 24hrs.

Recently, Fordham Professor of English and Creative Writing Caroline Hagood asked her students what would move them so much as to write on the nearest thing possible, as MLK had done writing his famous “Letters from Birmingham Jail” on top of old newspaper.

What would move you and your children so much to write on the nearest thing possible? Prove it in this mini challenge. Write a short simple statement about some belief, value, or idea that would inspire you to write vigorously on anything nearby. Eg the above MLK example, paper napkins and musical riffs for musicians, back of hand and poets. Make it brief but write with passion. Points for writing it with creative materials and/or on creative (but adult approved) surfaces.

#poetry #beauty #injustice #humanity #hope #community #whateversinyourheart
text:
￼MINI CHALLENGE - WRITE YOUR PASSION. 24hrs.

Recently, Fordham Professor of English and Creative Writing Caroline Hagood asked her students what would move them so much as to write on the nearest thing possible, as MLK had done writing his famous “Letters from Birmingham Jail” on top of old newspaper.

What would move you and your children so much to write on the nearest thing possible? Prove it in this mini challenge. Write a short simple statement about some belief, value, or idea that would inspire you to write vigorously on anything nearby. Eg the above MLK example, paper napkins and musical riffs for musicians, back of hand and poets. Make it brief but write with passion. Points for writing it with creative materials and/or on creative (but adult approved) surfaces.

#poetry #beauty #injustice #humanity #hope #community #whateversinyourheart

Please write a haiku

about your experience

social distancing

Haikus are short poems that follow a strict syllable structure. The first must be only 5 syllables. The second 7 syllables. And the third 5 again. For instance, if you couldn't tell the above instructions is a haiku.

For some background: each word has syllables. To find them, put your hand under your jaw. Every time your jaw moves down you count it as one syllable. How many syllables are in the word syllables? syll-a-bles. 3! Please be as creative as possible with this assignment and write as many as you want! We will repost our favorite!☺️💙 Here is an inspirational haiku

Good luck to you all!

I know you will impress us

You do that each day

shared_text:
Self Development Preschool
March 19 at 7:22 PM ·

🐛 🚵🏼‍♀️🦋A caterpillar’s journey can teach so much--the science of the life cycle, for instance. In fact, every year at Self Development Preschool we teach our four year old children this concept, relishing in the sheer joy in each child as they watch something cocooned away for a month turn into something so beautiful. But this year it’s teaching us something too.

As we social distance away in our cocoons, let’s try to become butterflies. Let’s commit to becoming the very best versions of ourselves. When it is over we will bravely fly into the world once again with a determined spirit, serving as an inspiration for others to do the same. But until the time we are butterflies, let’s use this as a time for self development. 🦋

Science Olympiad
Invitational – Casteel High School
January 18, 2020

The SDA – Mesa Science Olympiad Team participated in the Invitational Competition on Saturday, January 18, 2020. The competition consisted of 18 events. Several students placed in the events. Congratulations to our Science Olympiad Team!

Results
Mission Impossible 3rd Place
David, Dae-Guen, & Martin

Elastic Launch Glider 6th Place
Liam & Wyatt

Dynamic Planet 2nd Place
Dae-Guen & Connor

Mouse Trap Car 6th Place
Tristan & Wyatt

Destiny Lab 2nd Place
Martin & Tristan

Ping Pong Parachute 9th Place Aidan & Tristan

Write It Do It 8th Place
Liantsoa & Nalanie

Thank you to Mr. Mitchell and Ms. Strong for leading the Science Olympiad and Mrs. Harguess for attending Invitationals. We are looking forward to the Regionals!

post_text:
🦃🍁🍽💫HAPPY THANKSGIVING!! 🦃🍁🍽

💫We asked our kids what it meant to be “grateful.” Their answers gave the staff shivers. We found such bright minds and mature hearts. Here are some we thought we’d share:

“I like to feel grateful because it keeps me humble.”

“It’s important to be grateful so we can make others feel nice.”

“If you aren’t grateful, you can become bitter and mean. So we need to be grateful so we can live a nice, fair, and thankful life.”

🧡🧡🖤🧡❤️🧡🖤🧡🧡
We are so grateful to have such breathtakingly thoughtful and genuinely caring students here.

🧡HAPPY THANKSGIVING!! What are you all grateful for this year? 🧡

post_text: 💫🐬How do you make school a place kids *want* to go to? You make it as magical as their imagination. 💫🦄That’s what the Phoenix campus did! They transformed their school building into an 🌊underwater🌊wonder world! Each classroom, each hallway, every. single. wall. was covered with fish, coral, octopi. 🐟🦈Teachers dressed as sea creatures and for two days the campus pretended to be that far oft place of enchantment. 🧜🏼‍♀️🧜🏼‍♂️For two days we honored the phrase that leads to discovery and innovation: “why not?” 🐳🐙🐢

post_text:
🙌🏼🎓Congratulations to the Self Development Academy – Mesa Class of 2019! We had a quite a few impressive awards to give out: lifelong learner awards 🥇, scholarships 🥇, and a resiliency award 🥇!

⭐️The Class of 2019 had a record number of Lifelong Learners. 20 students began their elementary education journey with Self Development Preschool or Self Development Academy.
⭐️Here is to this year’s scholarship winners – Elesh, Tijana, Nathan, and Emma! Las Sendas Cardiology sponsors scholarships for students that contribute positively to the school culture and campus. 🥳 Congratulations to our scholarship recipients and thank you to Las Sendas Cardiology!
🥳Congratulations to this year’s Resiliency Award recipient – Khai’dra. The Gau Family sponsors this award scholarship.

😻We are so proud of our students! Best wishes in high school!💫💜
